qas.question: What are some states join Armenia in the Council of Europe?
When can the EU expect Armenia to attempt to join it?

context: Armenia is also a member of the Council of Europe, maintaining friendly relations with the European Union, especially with its member states such as <a2_0>France and Greece<a2_0/>. A 2005 survey reported that <a0_0>64%<a0_0/> of Armenia's population would be in favor of joining the EU. Several Armenian officials have also expressed the desire for their country to eventually become an EU member state, some[who?] predicting that it will make an official bid for membership <a3_0>in a few years<a3_0/>.[citation needed] In 2004 its forces joined KFOR, <a1_0>a NATO-led international force in Kosovo<a1_0/>. It is also an observer member of the Eurasian Economic Community and the Non-Aligned Movement.
